  "prompt": "Has the fear of a non wanted pregnancy, as no anticonceptive method is 100% fireproof, ever hindered your desire to have sexual intercourse?",
  "response": "Many people do experience anxiety or fear regarding unintended pregnancies, which can affect their desire for sexual intercourse. Concerns about contraceptive effectiveness, personal readiness for parenthood, or potential life changes can create feelings of apprehension. Open communication with partners and education about contraceptive options can help mitigate these fears and enhance sexual well-being. Ultimately, individual experiences vary widely, and it's important to consider personal circumstances and feelings.",
